New Records: Travis Head scored 80 off 25 balls, the highest first powerplay score in a T20I match.
Australia won the match by 7 wickets with 62 balls to spare.
Key Match Events: Australia completed a rapid win inside 10 overs.
Travis Head and Mitchell Marsh scored heavily after an early wicket loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in Edinburgh.
Mark Watt took two important wickets for Australia.
